    <section id="installation" class="mb-20 text-sm">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Installation</h2>
      <p class="mb-2">
        1. Install tailwind via CDN or with your gemfile

        <div class="ml-2">
          <p class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-700">Gemfile</p>
          <pre class="bg-slate-900 text-slate-100 p-4 rounded w-fit"><code class="text-xs text-blue-400"><code class="text-pink-400">./bin/bundle</code> add tailwindcss-ruby <br><code class="text-pink-400">./bin/bundle</code> add tailwindcss-rails <br><code class="text-pink-400">./bin/rails</code> tailwindcss:install</code></pre>
          <p class="mb-1 mt-1 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-700">CDN script</p>
          <pre class="bg-slate-900 text-slate-100 p-4 rounded w-fit"><code class="text-xs">&lt;script src="https://unpkg.com/@tailwindcss/browser@4"&gt;&lt;script&gt;</code></pre>
        </div>
     
      </p>
      <p class="my-2 w-[70%]">
        2. Go to this github <a class="text-blue-700 hover:underline" target="_blank" href="https://github.com/SM-16/Rails-elements-free">repository</a> and clone it. Add the components folder to your<%= render "static_pages/components/kbd", name:"app/views"%>
        folder. You can add the animations.css file to <%= render "static_pages/components/kbd", name:"app/stylesheets"%> 
      </p>
